			<h3 ><a href="#p56539"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=56539&amp;sid=c33a0885672e71cb93e027343bbfaab0#p56539"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1200&amp;sid=c33a0885672e71cb93e027343bbfaab0">Todemesne</a></strong> &raquo; August 29th, 2008, 3:58 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">Okay, I forgot to add that my Roombas run every day, sometimes twice in the kitchen area. With two messy cats this enables me to keep a level of cleanliness that I could never achieve with my Dyson.
<br />
<br />With that amount of use I am not really surprised that my Roombas die an early death.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_twisted.gif" alt=":twisted:" title="Twisted Evil" /></div>

			

